I agree with everything except abbreviations, but to be honest, I think my worst habit it just trying to use words with the same number of characters for different variables so they align well with monospace font.<p>e.g.<p><pre><code>    int num = 42;
    int acc = 0;
</code></pre>
instead of;<p><pre><code>    int n = 42;
    int acc = 0;
</code></pre>
and it gets worse when things get complicated;<p><pre><code>    vector<int> dist;  // stands for distances
    vector<int> excs;  // stands for excesses
</code></pre>
Does anyone else have this problem?
